---
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Stage from "~/components/Stage.astro";
---

<Section id="verification-leakage" num="13" title="The leakage record L(q)">
  <p>
    The previous section sorted what the server can and can't observe.
    This section is about <em>how we know that list is complete</em>.
  </p>
  <p>
    A BitcoinPIR client emits a sequence of wire rounds for every
    query — request bytes out, response bytes back, repeated round by
    round. An honest-but-curious server records the whole transcript:
    how many rounds happened, how big each request and response was,
    what items each request asked for. The verification effort defines
    exactly which bits of this transcript are allowed to vary across
    queries — that's the leakage record <code>L(q)</code> — and proves
    that everything else is fixed by the protocol.
  </p>

  <h3>The four fields of <code>L</code></h3>
  <p>
    Two fields are intentional public metadata that the protocol
    publishes as part of its API; the other two are pinned to
    constants by closure invariants in the implementation.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong><code>query_db_id</code></strong> — which database the
      query is against (the mainnet snapshot, a particular delta
      epoch, etc.). Intentional public metadata: choosing a DB to
      query is a visible part of the protocol's API.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong><code>session_query_index</code></strong> — the position
      of this query inside the HarmonyPIR session, used to schedule
      hint refresh. Function of session length, already public.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong><code>index_max_items_per_group_per_level</code></strong>
      — pinned to <code>2</code> by the <em>INDEX Merkle Group-Symmetry</em>
      invariant. Multi-query batches are routed across all three
      candidate PBC groups via <code>pbc_plan_rounds</code>, so
      colliding scripthashes never accumulate items in a single group.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong><code>chunk_max_items_per_group_per_level</code></strong>
      — pinned to <code>1</code> (with <code>M = 16</code> Merkle
      items per query and <code>K_CHUNK = 80</code> PBC groups) by the
      <em>CHUNK Merkle Item-Count Symmetry</em> invariant. Real chunk
      IDs fill the prefix of a 16-slot buffer; per-query synthetic IDs
      derived from
      <code>SHA-256("BPIR-CHUNK-PAD" || scripthash || query_index)</code>
      fill the suffix. Every query — found, not-found, whale —
      contributes exactly 16 items, and the synthetic IDs are spread
      uniformly over the chunk-id space so batched CHUNK rounds pack
      densely.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The simulator-property claim</h3>
  <p>
    For any backend <code>b</code> and any two queries
    <code>q1, q2</code> with <code>L(q1) = L(q2)</code>, the wire
    transcripts of <code>Real(b, q1)</code> and <code>Real(b, q2)</code>
    are equal. The visualization below is what that looks like in
    practice — a found query and a not-found query that happen to
    share the same <code>L</code>, side by side.
  </p>

  <Stage
    caption="Two queries with the same L produce wire transcripts that match byte-for-byte across every round. The byte-diff stays at zero, even when one query found the address and the other did not."
    label="Byte-identity demo"
  >
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 320" role="img"
      aria-label="Top half: two L records side by side, with all four fields equal. Bottom half: two wire transcripts side by side. Identity markers between them. Aggregate byte-diff is zero."
      data-anim="byte-identity">

      <defs>
        <marker id="vi-arr" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="5" refY="9"
          markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 5 9 L 10 0 z" fill="var(--fg-muted)"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>

      <!-- L(q1) -->
      <g class="lrec lrec-1">
        <text x="160" y="14" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11"
          fill="var(--fg-muted)">L(q1) — FOUND, sh = 0xa1b2…</text>
        <rect x="40" y="22" width="240" height="86" rx="6"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--accent)"/>
        <text x="56" y="40" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">db_id            : 0</text>
        <text x="56" y="56" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">session_index    : 7</text>
        <text x="56" y="72" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">index_max_items  : 2</text>
        <text x="56" y="88" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">chunk_max_items  : 1</text>
      </g>

      <!-- L(q2) -->
      <g class="lrec lrec-2">
        <text x="520" y="14" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11"
          fill="var(--fg-muted)">L(q2) — NOT-FOUND, sh = 0xc3d4…</text>
        <rect x="400" y="22" width="240" height="86" rx="6"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--accent)"/>
        <text x="416" y="40" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">db_id            : 0</text>
        <text x="416" y="56" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">session_index    : 7</text>
        <text x="416" y="72" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">index_max_items  : 2</text>
        <text x="416" y="88" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">chunk_max_items  : 1</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Equality marker between L records -->
      <g class="leq">
        <rect x="298" y="48" width="84" height="34" rx="6"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--ok)"/>
        <text x="340" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11"
          font-weight="700" fill="var(--ok)">L(q1) = L(q2)</text>
        <text x="340" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9"
          fill="var(--fg-muted)">field-by-field</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Down arrows from L records to transcripts -->
      <path d="M 160 110 L 160 142" stroke="var(--fg-muted)"
        stroke-width="1" fill="none" marker-end="url(#vi-arr)"/>
      <path d="M 520 110 L 520 142" stroke="var(--fg-muted)"
        stroke-width="1" fill="none" marker-end="url(#vi-arr)"/>

      <!-- Transcript headers -->
      <text x="160" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
        font-weight="600" fill="var(--fg)">Wire transcript</text>
      <text x="520" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
        font-weight="600" fill="var(--fg)">Wire transcript</text>
      <text x="340" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
        fill="var(--fg-muted)">byte diff</text>

      <!-- Round 1: INDEX phase -->
      <g class="trace-row tr-1">
        <rect x="40" y="166" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="50" y="181" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">INDEX phase  · K = 75 PBC groups</text>
        <text class="eq-mark" x="340" y="183" text-anchor="middle"
          font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="var(--ok)">≡</text>
        <rect x="400" y="166" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="410" y="181" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">INDEX phase  · K = 75 PBC groups</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Round 2: CHUNK phase -->
      <g class="trace-row tr-2">
        <rect x="40" y="194" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="50" y="209" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">CHUNK phase  · M = 16 items (padded)</text>
        <text class="eq-mark" x="340" y="211" text-anchor="middle"
          font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="var(--ok)">≡</text>
        <rect x="400" y="194" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="410" y="209" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">CHUNK phase  · M = 16 items (padded)</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Round 3: MERKLE phase -->
      <g class="trace-row tr-3">
        <rect x="40" y="222" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="50" y="237" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">MERKLE phase · per-level siblings</text>
        <text class="eq-mark" x="340" y="239" text-anchor="middle"
          font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="var(--ok)">≡</text>
        <rect x="400" y="222" width="240" height="22" rx="4"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--border)"/>
        <text x="410" y="237" font-size="10"
          font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--fg)">MERKLE phase · per-level siblings</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Aggregate diff bar -->
      <g transform="translate(40,260)">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="600" height="32" rx="6"
          fill="var(--bg-elev-2)" stroke="var(--ok)"/>
        <text x="300" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12"
          font-weight="700" fill="var(--ok)">aggregate byte-diff across full transcript: 0</text>
      </g>
      <text x="340" y="306" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9"
        fill="var(--fg-muted)" font-style="italic">
        Asserted by leakage_integration_test.rs · *_found_vs_not_found_have_byte_identical_profiles
      </text>
    </svg>
  </Stage>

  <p>
    The picture answers <em>what</em> the verification claims. The
    next page covers <em>how</em> we believe it — three layers of
    evidence, each addressing a different way the claim could be
    wrong.
  </p>
</Section>

<style>
  /* Subtle pulse on the equality markers; respects reduced-motion. */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    [data-anim="byte-identity"] .leq rect {
      animation: vi-pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    [data-anim="byte-identity"] .eq-mark {
      animation: vi-pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    [data-anim="byte-identity"] .tr-2 .eq-mark { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
    [data-anim="byte-identity"] .tr-3 .eq-mark { animation-delay: 0.8s; }
  }
  @keyframes vi-pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 0.55; }
    50%      { opacity: 1; }
  }
</style>
